  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of the study is to demonstrate the non-inferiority for clinical efficacy of an
      endovascular treatment strategy with the MitraClip® in comparison with a surgical treatment
      strategy in patients with severe primary mitral regurgitation judged eligible for anatomical
      repair with the MitraClip® or mitral valve surgery with high surgical risk.

      This trial is a French, multicenter and randomized trial. Patients enrolled will be
      clinically followed for 2 years ( clinical visit at 1 month, at 6 months and 12 months, phone
      call at 18 months and clincial visit at 24 months).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
